      "beat_id": "B05",
      "t_start": 37.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "Ten to the minus thirty-five meters. For comparison, a proton has radius ten to the minus fifteen meters. Your quantum wavelength is twenty orders of magnitude smaller than a proton. No slit, grating, or crystal anywhere in the universe has spacings this small.",
