      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "Large molecules do diffract \u2014 just barely. A carbon-sixty buckyball has wavelength about two point five picometers, smaller than the molecule itself. Zeilinger's Vienna group made it diffract through a grating in 1999. The fringes were real, but the slit had to be only fifty nanometers wide.",
