      "t_start": 77.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "The classical world is not a different regime of physics. It is the limit where the wavelength is so small that no available grating can reveal the wave structure. Quantum mechanics never stops applying \u2014 it just becomes undetectable as mass and speed grow.",
